Rating: 4
The most efficient way I know of to make a lemon curd is in the microwave. Use a deep glass bowl, cook at high power and whisk frequently. My microwave has a temperature probe, which takes the guess work out of knowing when it is done (although it was quite easy to tell when the consistency was right). Try it, you will soon say good-bye to the double boiler. Very nice recipe, guests were pleased (skipped whipped cream topping as mentioned by others - didn't seem necessary).

Rating: 4
